<text id="02-output-contract" title="JPA / Hibernate Output Contract" version="1.1.0" est_tokens="900" depth="essential">
  <summary>JSON Schema for the JPA-layer manifest this methodology produces. Validator enforces required keys + per-field constraints.</summary>

  <section title="Schema">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://faion.net/schemas/java-jpa-hibernate.json",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["spring_boot_version", "ddl_auto", "open_in_view", "entities", "migrations_paired", "fetch_audit"],
  "properties": {
    "spring_boot_version": {"type": "string", "pattern": "^3\\."},
    "ddl_auto": {"const": "validate"},
    "open_in_view": {"const": false},
    "entities": {
      "type": "array",
      "minItems": 1,
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["class", "business_key", "associations_lazy", "uses_lombok_data"],
        "properties": {
          "class": {"type": "string"},
          "business_key": {"type": "string", "minLength": 1},
          "associations_lazy": {"type": "boolean", "const": true},
          "uses_lombok_data": {"type": "boolean", "const": false}
        }
      }
    },
    "migrations_paired": {"type": "boolean", "const": true},
    "fetch_audit": {
      "type": "object",
      "required": ["eager_associations_found"],
      "properties": {
        "eager_associations_found": {"type": "array", "items": {"type": "string"}, "maxItems": 0}
      }
    },
    "forbidden_patterns_found": {"type": "array", "items": {"type": "string"}, "maxItems": 0}
  }
}
]]></code>
  </section>

  <example valid="true">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "spring_boot_version": "3.2.1",
  "ddl_auto": "validate",
  "open_in_view": false,
  "entities": [
    {"class": "com.acme.billing.Invoice", "business_key": "invoiceNumber", "associations_lazy": true, "uses_lombok_data": false}
  ],
  "migrations_paired": true,
  "fetch_audit": {"eager_associations_found": []},
  "forbidden_patterns_found": []
}
]]></code>
  </example>

  <example valid="false">
    <code lang="json"><![CDATA[
{
  "spring_boot_version": "2.7.0",
  "ddl_auto": "update",
  "open_in_view": true,
  "entities": [{"class": "com.acme.billing.Invoice", "business_key": "", "associations_lazy": false, "uses_lombok_data": true}],
  "migrations_paired": false,
  "fetch_audit": {"eager_associations_found": ["Invoice.lines"]},
  "forbidden_patterns_found": ["CascadeType.ALL on @ManyToOne in Invoice.customer"]
}
]]></code>
    <note>Spring Boot 2.x; ddl-auto auto-mutates; OSIV on; no business key; @Data on entity; eager fetch + cascade ALL on ManyToOne; migrations missing.</note>
  </example>

  <section title="Forbidden patterns">
    <list>
      <item>`@Data` (Lombok) on a JPA entity.</item>
      <item>`FetchType.EAGER` on any association.</item>
      <item>`cascade = CascadeType.ALL` on a `@ManyToOne` relationship.</item>
      <item>Entity diff without a paired Flyway migration.</item>
      <item>`@Modifying` without `clearAutomatically = true` for bulk updates/deletes.</item>
    </list>
  </section>

  <reference path="scripts/validate-java-jpa-hibernate.py">Validator script</reference>
</text>
